pan class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 10/22/02 12:11:05 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> Re: The American Death Trap</span><hr size=1> <br>
        I really doubt that movies, films have anything to do with it.  Hollywood films are seen just as much in Europe as they are in the US.<br>
      Guns are too available in the US.  Some states have as many Gun shops as they have cady stores, if not more.   Different states have different gun laws.  Some very strict and others very free.   Having strict gun laws in one state doesn't help since anyone can drive to another state and freely get what they want. <br>
        Federal law which is for all the states is very loose as far as gun control.   Many feel it is anti-constitutional because the US Constitution states that we have the right to bear arms.  Because of that, it is very difficult to have federal anti-gun laws passed as many play on that fact.  <br>
         And then there is the National Rifle Association, Charlton Heston(Moses, Planet of the Apes)who is president of that association.  It is very powerfull and gives a lot of money to republican political campaigns.  Bush and him are probably best friends.  Republicans are surely not going to support anti-gun laws and cut off there money supply.<br>
          There are unstable people all over the world.  You give these people the freedom to buy guns and you get the results we have here, free for all shootings, innocent people shot left and right.<br>
           In a way, I guess we can blame it partially on Hollywood, since Charlton Heston was a movie actor and big film star in his time. <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCE6FF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bbbarden.showUserPublicProfile?gid=confound>CoNfOuNd</A> </span><br><BR><img src=http://peter.armo.co.uk/img/irish.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60><br> <span class=usertitle>Createur de Projets<br /><img src='http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-admin.gif' /><br /><img src='http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-vip.gif' /></span><br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 10/22/02 4:27:26 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> Re: The American Death Trap</span><hr size=1> I don't think it has anything to do with violence on tv, as all other countries now have access to these things. Movies that were banned when they got released are now fine to be shown on tv. Attitudes have changed, and violence, sex, and killings are suitable for tv. How effective the 9pm watershed is I don't know.<br>
<br>
I think we need to look more at the laws, as well as why people do these awful acts. Now Americans have tried to persuade me why they need these guns. People have told me its incase some mad man calls to their door. Well, generally we have safety locks, and alarms, and police lines. If you don't feel that the area you live in isn't safe, I really don't think people should live there. I think it's more scary having someone mad turn up at your door with a gun, than having someone mad turn up at your door without one. Then, are you really going to use a gun if you are in such a situation?<br>
<br>
They have a knife. You have your gun. Now, I have also been told that the gun isn't to kill the person, just to wound them. Ok, so you shoot them in the balls and they fall down, but is that self defence? Maybe American courts are different.<br>
<br>
I would think that if no one had guns, you wouldn't need to be scared in the first place, so you wouldn't need a gun. Licensed guns are fine. If people want to go and shoot birds or something stupid and pointless I am not going to stop them, but guns that aren't counted, aren't monitored, and you are not even on a list when you buy one? Am I right? <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bbbarden.showUserPublicProfile?gid=s4turn3>S4TuRn3</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://digilander.iol.it/gar1/icon/fantasia/stripe.gif" BORDER=0> </span><br><BR><img src=http://www.syntax-web.net/img/satel.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60><br> <span class=usertitle>On another planet<br /><img src='http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-mod.gif' /></span><br>  ezSupporter<br></td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 10/22/02 8:29:31 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> Re: The American Death Trap</span><hr size=1> Won't comment this. Some might say I judge americans without knowing... <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this mes